resources.string: Two roads diverged in a yellow wood, And sorry I could not travel both And be one traveler, long I stood And looked down one as far as I could To where it bent in the undergrowth; by Foster
The apparition of these faces in the crowd; Petals on a wet, black bough; by Ezra pound
No desire opens me: I am full, I never close myself with refusal- in the rhythm of my daily soul I do not desire-I am moved; by Rilke
